prisonescape.game.screens.components
Class HUD

java.lang.Object
  prisonescape.game.screens.components.HUD

public class HUD
extends java.lang.Object

HUD creates the Heads Up Display which is displayed on all playable screens. The current version displays the name of the current area the player is in, the time, current objectives and the inventory. HUD also facilitates the Sleeping UI where a player can interact with a "SLEEP" object such as a bed, which brings up the Sleeping window allowing the player to select a time for them to sleep until.

Constructor Detail

HUD

public HUD(GameController controller)
Constructor for the HUD class.

Creates the table in which other HUD elements are placed into, and then added onto the Scene2d stage for it to be rendered onto the screen.

Also calls the methods which creates any other HUD elements such as the quest tracker and inventory.

Parameters:
g - of type PrisonEscapeGame is taken as a parameter to help in setting the time for the game in the Sleeping UI

The update method is used to actively update any HUD elements that need to be changed.

Updates the area name, time, items in the inventory and the value on the Sleeping UI.

checkItems

public void checkItems(Item i)
Checks the given item against a list of story items required in the game. If all items are found, the items are combined into a new item, the parts are removed and the state and objective is updated.

Parameters:
i - Takes an Item in order to check if it's a required story item
